0had%20been%20gathering%20momentum%20since%20the%20Abraham%20Accords%20of%202020%2C%20but%20one%20of%20the%20first%20diplomatic%20casualties%20of%20the%20war%20was%20Saudi%20Arabia%20pausing%20talks%20with%20the%20country.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20deadly%20attack%20on%20a%20Gaza%20hospital%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20which%20killed%20500%20and%20whose%20origins%20are%20disputed%2C%20worsened%20the%20situation%20and%20Jordan%20announced%20the%20cancellation%20of%20a%20scheduled%20meeting%20between%20US%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20and%20Jordan's%20King%20Abdullah%2C%20Egypt's%20President%20Abdel%20Fattah%20El-Sisi%20and%20Palestinian%20Authority%20President%20Mahmoud%20Abbas%20on%20Wednesday.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20West%20has%20been%20standing%20firmly%20behind%20Israel%20and%20Mr%20Biden%20said%20that%20the%20hospital%20attack%20seemed%20to%20have%20been%20carried%20out%20by%20the%20%26quot%3Bother%20team%26quot%3B%2C%20Saudi%20Arabia%2C%20UAE%2C%20Bahrain%2C%20Egypt%2C%20Jordan%20and%20Turkey%20have%20blamed%20Israel%20for%20the%20attack.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Nakba%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFor%20Palestinians%20and%20Arabs%2C%20the%20war%20with%20Israel%20did%20not%20begin%20on%20the%20morning%20of%20October%207%2C%20when%20Hamas%20launched%205%2C000%20rockets%20into%20the%20country%2C%20coupled%20with%20a%20land%20and%20sea%20attack.%20For%20them%2C%20the%20war%20has%20been%20going%20on%20since%201948%2C%20when%20militias%20expelled%20Palestinians%20from%20their%20homes%20and%20killed%20tens%20of%20thousands%20in%20what%20is%20called%20the%20Nakba%2C%20or%20catastrophe.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%201948%20Arab-Israeli%20War%20was%20the%20first%20conflict%20between%20the%20Arab%20World%20and%20the%20newly%20independent%20country.%20Israel%20declared%20its%20independence%20on%20May%2014%2C%201948%20-%20after%20the%20United%20Nations'%20partition%20proposal%20for%20Palestine%20-%20and%20a%20civil%20war%20which%20was%20raging%20in%20what%20was%20called%20Mandatory%20Palestine%20until%20then%2C%20escalated%20into%20a%20conflict%20between%20Israel%20and%20Arab%20states.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20military%20coalition%20of%20five%20Arab%20countries%20-%20Egypt%2C%20Iraq%2C%20Jordan%2C%20Lebanon%2C%20and%20Syria%20-%20entered%20Palestine%20and%20the%20war%20ended%20with%20the%20permanent%20displacement%20of%20more%20than%20half%20of%20the%20Palestinian%20population%20and%20Israel%20controlling%20almost%2060%25%20of%20the%20area%20proposed%20by%20the%20UN%20for%20the%20Palestinian%20state.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EVicious%20Cycle%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20relationship%20between%20Israel%20and%20its%20Arab%20neighbours%20continued%20to%20remain%20poor%20after%20an%20armistice%20was%20signed%20in%201949%20and%20worsened%20after%20the%20Suez%20Crisis%20of%201956.%20In%20May%201967%2C%20Egypt%20announced%20that%20the%20Straits%20of%20Tiran%20would%20be%20closed%20to%20Israeli%20vessels%20and%20this%20was%20one%20of%20the%20catalysts%20for%20the%20Six-Day%20War%20a%20month%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20during%20the%20Six-Day%20War%20that%20the%20Israel%20military%20launched%20a%20ground%20offensive%20into%20Egypt's%20Sinai%20Peninsula%20and%20the%20Egyptian-occupied%20Gaza%20Strip%2C%20which%20is%20the%20focal%20point%20of%20the%20current%20war%2C%20over%20half%20a%20century%20later.%20The%20war%20saw%20the%20involvement%20of%20Egypt%2C%20Jordan%20and%20Syria.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EEgypt%20lost%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%20to%20Israel%2C%20Syria%20lost%20the%20Golan%20Heights%20and%20Jordan%20lost%20control%20of%20East%20Jerusalem%20and%20the%20West%20Bank%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAnother%20war%20took%20place%20in%201969%20and%20was%20followed%20by%20the%20Yom%20Kippur%20or%20Ramadan%20War%20of%201973.%20This%20was%20fought%20between%20Israel%2C%20Egypt%20and%20Syria%20and%20also%20saw%20the%20US%20and%20the%20Soviet%20Union%2C%20who%20were%20locked%20in%20the%20Cold%20War%2C%20aiding%20opposite%20sides.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EArab%20Nationalism%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20repeated%20wars%20with%20Israel%20and%20the%20loss%20of%20land%20to%20it%20-%20not%20only%20in%20Palestine%20but%20from%20other%20nations%20as%20well%20-%20has%20been%20a%20festering%20sore%20for%20the%20Arab%20psyche.%20In%20the%201950s%20and%20the%201960s%2C%20the%20heyday%20of%20Arab%20nationalism%2C%20Palestine%20was%20the%20central%20Arab%20cause%20which%20catapulted%20many%20Arab%20leaders%20to%20power%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPopular%20and%20public%20support%20in%20many%20Arab%20nations%20is%20for%20an%20independent%20Palestinian%20state%20and%20many%20leaders%20who%20have%20spoken%20for%20normalised%20ties%20with%20Israel%20have%20had%20to%20pay%20a%20price.%20On%20July%2020%2C%201951%2C%20Jordanian%20King%20Abdullah%20I%20was%20assassinated%20on%20the%20steps%20of%20one%20of%20the%20holiest%20shrines%20of%20Islam%2C%20the%20al-Aqsa%20Mosque%20in%20Jerusalem%2C%20during%20Friday%20prayers%2C%20by%20a%20Palestinian%20opposed%20to%20Jordan's%20tolerance%20of%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EEgyptian%20president%20Anwar%20Sadat%20was%20assassinated%20in%201981%20by%20militants%20who%20were%20against%20the%20peace%20deal%20with%20Israel.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAnother%20key%20aspect%20is%20religion.%20The%20Al%20Aqsa%20Mosque%20in%20Jerusalem%20is%20the%20third%20holiest%20site%20in%20Islam%20and%20Israel-occupied%20territories%20are%20home%20to%20several%20other%20Islamic%20holy%20sites.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAbraham%20Accords%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Abraham%20Accords%20of%202020%20between%20Israel%2C%20Bahrain%20and%20the%20UAE%20marked%20a%20turning%20point%20in%20ties%20between%20Israel%20and%20the%20Arab%20countries.%20Saudi%20Arabia%2C%20which%20had%20developed%20extensive%20business%20and%20military%20relationships%20with%20Israel%2C%20was%20also%20in%20talks%20with%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMany