urt%20to%20recognise%20a%20constitutional%20right%20to%20marry.%20The%20right%20to%20state-sanctioned%20marriage%20has%20already%20been%20granted%20by%20the%20same%20legislature%20the%20court%20otherwise%20seems%20comfortable%20deferring%20to%2C%20granted%20under%20the%20secular%20regime%20that%20is%20the%20Special%20Marriage%20Act.%20The%20primary%20issue%20before%20the%20court%2C%20by%20its%20own%20determination%2C%20was%20more%20limited%20%E2%80%93%20under%20that%20secular%20regime%2C%20once%20the%20right%20to%20marry%20is%20recognised%2C%20is%20it%20permissible%20for%20it%20to%20be%20extended%20to%20heterosexual%20couples%20but%20not%20to%20homosexual%20couples%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20question%2C%20then%2C%20was%20not%20whether%20%3Cem%3Ede%20novo%20%3C%2Fem%3Ea%20same-sex%20couple%20can%20claim%20that%20the%20state%20must%20recognise%20their%20right%20to%20marry.%20Instead%2C%20the%20right%20of%20same-sex%20couples%20to%20marry%20was%20being%20asserted%20in%20the%20context%20of%20the%20state%20choosing%20to%20recognise%20some%20marriages%20and%20not%20others%3B%20of%20privileging%20some%20intimacies%20and%20not%20others%3B%20of%20saying%20some%20people%20can%20make%20end-of-life%20decisions%20for%20those%20they%20love%20and%20not%20others.%20The%20court%20was%20not%20to%20answer%20whether%20the%20Constitution%20granted%20a%20right%20to%20marry%3B%20it%20was%20to%20answer%20whether%20the%20Constitution%20permitted%20such%20a%20right%20to%20be%20granted%20selectively.%20The%20court%20was%20not%20asked%20to%20legislate%20and%20create%20an%20institution%20where%20none%20existed%3B%20it%20was%20asked%20to%20ensure%20that%20access%20to%20institutions%20that%20the%20legislature%20has%20already%20recognised%20was%20non-discriminatory.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Two%20Steps%20Forward%2C%20Three%20Steps%20Back%3A%20Supreme%20Court%20Verdict%20on%20Marriage%20Equality%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Ftwo-steps-forward-three-steps-back-supreme-court-verdict-marriage-equality%5C%22%3ETwo%20Steps%20Forward%2C%20Three%20Steps%20Back%3A%20Supreme%20Court%20Verdict%20on%20Marriage%20Equality%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20fundamental%20task%2C%20the%20court%20has%20failed%20miserably.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20court%E2%80%99s%20fallacy%20is%20perhaps%20best%20demonstrated%20by%20examining%20an%20analogy%20the%20majority%20opinion%20uses%20%E2%80%93%20it%20reasons%20that%20just%20because%20there%20exists%20a%20right%20to%20movement%20does%20not%20entitle%20a%20petitioner%20to%20approach%20the%20court%20and%20seek%20the%20construction%20of%20a%20specific%20network%20of%20roads.%20The%20analogy%20captures%20the%20very%20core%20of%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20reasoning%20%E2%80%93%20the%20court%2C%20apparently%2C%20cannot%20by%20judicial%20diktat%20create%20laws%20or%20frameworks%20where%20none%20exist.%20That%20may%20well%20be%20the%20case.%20However%2C%20it%20seems%20to%20elude%20the%20court%20that%20a%20road%20has%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20already%20been%20constructed%20here%3B%20it%20needed%20only%20to%20declare%20that%20no%20citizens%20could%20then%20be%20denied%20access%20to%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EEqually%20regrettable%20is%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20hand-wringing%20about%20how%20polyvocality%20cannot%20be%20accommodated%20in%20a%20judicial%20setting%2C%20and%20consequently%20the%20court%20is%20an%20inappropriate%20forum%20for%20making%20decisions%20about%20complex%20social%20issues%20like%20same-sex%20marriage.%20Undoubtedly%2C%20same-sex%20marriage%20is%20an%20issue%20which%20divides%20opinion%20in%20the%20socio-political%20realities%20of%20India.%20Undoubtedly%2C%20it%20is%20desirable%20that%20consensus%20on%20this%20issue%20be%20gradually%20built%20on%20the%20ground%20so%20that%20society%E2%80%99s%20acceptance%20of%20evolving%20norms%20is%20deepened.%20Undoubtedly%2C%20the%20executive%20and%20legislature%20are%20better-placed%20than%20the%20judiciary%20to%20build%20and%20assess%20that%20consensus.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENone%20of%20this%20entitles%20the%20court%20to%20hold%20an%20individual%E2%80%99s%20rights%20hostage%20to%20the%20building%20of%20that%20consensus.%20Consensus-building%20matters%20because%20it%20enables%20a%20deeper%20percolation%20of%20constitutional%20norms%2C%20not%20because%20public%20opinion%20exists%20outside%20of%20and%20beyond%20constitutional%20norms.%20State%20discrimination%20against%20a%20minority%20can%20never%20be%20recognised%20by%20majority%20fiat.%20In%20the%20face%20of%20conflicting%20opinions%20about%20an%20individual%E2%80%99s%20constitutional%20rights%20(or%2C%20worse%2C%20unanimity%20about%20trampling%20on%20them)%2C%20the%20role%20of%20the%20court%20is%20to%20stand%20up%20for%20that%20individual.%20It%20cannot%20and%20must%20not%20be%20to%20relegate%20that%20individual%E2%80%99s%20rights%20to%20the%20realm%20of%20policy%20debate%20simply%20because%20many%20others%20differ%20about%20the%20nature%20of%20those%20rights%2C%20and%20by%20so%20relegating%20them%20to%20the%20realm%20of%20policy%20debate%20concede%20the%20field%20utterly%20to%20the%20majoritarian%20impulses%20of%20the%20legislature.%20Polyvocality%20matters%20when%20debating%20the%20finer%20points%20of%20where%20public%20money%20should%20best%20be%20spent%3B%20it%20does%20not%20matter%20while%20recognising%20that%20the%20state%20is%20denying%20a%20group%20of%20individuals%20their%20fundamental%20right%20to%20equality.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20judgement%20does%20not%20represent%20judicial%20restraint.%20It%20represents%20judicial%20abdication.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EKaustubh%20Chaturvedi%20is%20an%20advocate%20practising%20before%20various%20fora%20in%20Delhi.%20He%E2%80%99s%20an%20alumnus%20of%20the%20National%20Law%20School%20of%20India%20University%2C%20and%20can%20be%20contacted%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Akaustubhchaturvedi%40outlook.com%5C%22%3Ekaustubhchaturvedi%40outlook.com%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697713202000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F11%2F20110519%2FScreen-Shot-2021-11-20-at-11.05.05-AM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-courts-marriage-equality-judgment-represents-judicial-abdication%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20court%20was%20not%20asked%20to%20legislate%20and%20create%20an%20institution%20where%20none%20existed%3B%20it%20was%20asked%20to%20ensure%20that%20access%20to%20institutions%20that%20the%20legislature%20has%20already%20recognised%20was%20non-discriminatory.%20In%20this%20fundamental%20task%2C%20the%20court%20has%20failed%20miserably.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-courts-marriage-equality-judgment-represents-judicial-abdication%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Coforge%20Q2%20results%3A%20Net%20profit%20declines%2010%25%20to%20Rs%20181%20cr%2C%20revenue%20up%2016%25%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697712979000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2023-10%2F08%2Ffull%2F1696786897-685.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fresults%2Fcoforge-q2-results-net-profit-declines-10-to-rs-181-cr-revenue-up-16-123101900692_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Revenue%20from%20operations%20came%20in%20at%20Rs%202%2C276.2%20crore%20in%20the%20quarter%20under%20review%2C%20rising%20over%2016%20per%20cent%20from%20Rs%201%2C959.4%20crore%20in%20the%20corresponding%20period%20of%20the%20previous%20fiscal%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fresults%2Fcoforge-q2-results-net-profit-declines-10-to-rs-181-cr-revenue-up-16-123101900692_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.o