2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fsupreme-court-newsclick-arrests-chief-editor-prabir-purkayastha-hr-head-amit-chakraborty-240554%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20reported%20that%20a%20bench%20of%20Justices%20B.R.%20Gavai%20and%20Prashant%20Kumar%20Mishra%20was%20hearing%20the%20special%20leave%20petitions%20filed%20by%20Purkayastha%20and%20Chakraborty.%20The%20petitions%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fdelhi-hc-dismisses-newsclick-editor-hr-heads-pleas-challenging-remand-order%5C%22%3Echallenged%20the%20Delhi%20high%20court%E2%80%99s%20October%2013%20dismissal%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20petitions%20filed%20by%20the%20two.%20Justice%20Tushar%20Rao%20Gedela%20had%20upheld%20their%20seven-day%20police%20remand.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPurkayastha%20and%20Chakraborty%20were%20arrested%20in%20a%20Delhi%20Police%20Special%20Cell%20case%20in%20which%20the%20stringent%20Unlawful%20Activities%20(Prevention)%20Act%20is%20invoked.%20The%20arrests%20took%20place%20after%20raids%20on%20several%20journalists%20connected%20to%20%3Cem%3ENewsClick%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Police%20acted%20on%20a%20%3Cem%3ENew%20York%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20story%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fdelhi-police-terror-fir-against-newsclick-names-chinese-firms-xiaomi-vivo-puts-lawyers-in-crosshairs%5C%22%3Ewhich%20claims%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0that%C2%A0%3Cem%3ENewsClick%3C%2Fem%3E%20received%20Chinese%20funding%20to%20criticise%20the%20Indian%20government%E2%80%99s%20policies%20and%20promote%20Chinese%20propaganda.%20The%20portal%20has%20denied%20these%20allegations%20and%20said%20in%20court%20that%20they%20did%20not%20receive%20any%20money%20at%20all%20from%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAmerican%20millionaire%20Neville%20Roy%20Singham%2C%20who%20has%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Ffull-statement-neville-roy-singham-rejects-allegations-in-the-newsclick-case-as-misleading%5C%22%3Enamed%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20an%20accused%20in%20the%20case%2C